Q24. What is the purpose of this in JavaScript?
------------------------------------------------
this refers to the current object that is executing the function.
Example
let person = {
  name: "Mahesh",
  greet: function(){
    console.log("Hello " + this.name);
  }
};
person.greet();
Output
Hello Mahesh
Here this.name refers to person.name.
Q25. What is Hoisting in JavaScript?
----------------------------------------
Hoisting means JavaScript moves variable and function declarations to the top of their scope before execution.
Example
console.log(a);
var a = 10;
Output
undefined
Because JavaScript interprets it like this:
var a;
console.log(a);
a = 10;
Function Hoisting Example
hello();
function hello(){
  console.log("Hello");
}
Output
Hello
Function declarations are fully hoisted.
